- Install TypeScript ESLint using `npm install --save-dev @typescript-eslint/parser @typescript-eslint/eslint-plugin`
- Use the latest version of ESLint by running `npm update eslint`
- Configure ESLint with a `.eslintrc.json` file:
  ```json
  {
    "parser": "@typescript-eslint/parser",
    "plugins": ["@typescript-eslint"],
    "extends": [
      "eslint:recommended",
      "plugin:@typescript-eslint/recommended"
    ],
    "rules": {
      // Custom rules here
    }
  }
  ```
- Integrate Prettier for code formatting by installing `npm install --save-dev eslint-config-prettier eslint-plugin-prettier`
- Add Prettier to ESLint configuration:
  ```json
  {
    "extends": [
      "eslint:recommended",
      "plugin:@typescript-eslint/recommended",
      "prettier"
    ],
    "plugins": ["@typescript-eslint", "prettier"],
    "rules": {
      "prettier/prettier": "error"
    }
  }
  ```
- Run ESLint with `npx eslint yourfile.ts` or for an entire project, use `npx eslint .`
- Use the `--fix` flag to automatically fix linting errors: `npx eslint yourfile.ts --fix`
